social_posts.post_text:
May the Holy Spirit fill the room today as Jack testifies on Capitol Hill to discuss the direct correlation between fatherlessness and gun violence.

Photos posted are of a day earlier this year when our friends Rep Owens and Rep Donalds introduced the Fatherhood Resolution, a legislation Jack has been working on for years. 

I’m just humbled to be surrounded by these warriors. God is so good to allow me to be a witness to this.

I cannot wait to see this Fatherhood Bill pass in 2023!

(Also, yes, I really like my sassy pink suit too.)

Here I am again, a very delayed post. Here’s just a small post sharing some of our Holiday activities here in Florida. I am so happy to be in south FL, where we’re surrounded by people we love, people who sharpen us. We are also able to serve alongside our best friends like Jesus did. From hurricane relief, to the teaching kids, to meal deliveries, and prison ministry, (and so much more I’m not listing) JBF has made this holiday season so memorable for us and I’m so glad God called us here. Michael and I are grateful to work and serve alongside the Brewers and The Jack Brewer Foundation. ❤️

Head to @thejackbrewerfoundation page or @jackbrewerbsi’s page if you don’t follow already. I’m terrible at posting, but the work is amazing 🙏🏼

Happy 40th to my husband Michael.
I’m so proud to be your wife and see you grow as a humble servant to God, a leader of our house, a devoted husband, and more than anything, I’ve loved watching you turn into a father. ❤️

Turning 40 is quite a milestone. To be able to celebrate it with the birth of our son is beyond words. My bride @jilliealexis has been an absolute superstar when it comes to motherhood. I love our King family and cannot wait to see what God has in store for the next 40 years. 🤜🏼🤛🏼

I left my first job at Fox News to go on The Bachelor and I had the opportunity to go on Fox News to discuss the impact of social media following my appearances on The Bachelor.. full circle moment thanks to my friend @brigidmarymcd.

I rarely post so here’s a long caption:

Following the show, there were a flood of opinions that impacted the way I thought about myself, it changed the way I acted, the way I dressed and portrayed myself on social media. Thankfully God quickly rescued me from caring about what others think, I care about what He thinks of me, not the world.

I see a lot of people on these platforms chasing “likes.” Most of these people are women (too many wives and mothers which breaks my heart) exploiting themselves, looking for validation from the world.

People are too often trying to get the right picture to promote some agenda or idea, with the right people, in the right setting, all to boost their status and popularity among strangers really. 

Social media can be a dangerous place where satanic ideas flood the internet, and sinful lifestyles are promoted. It can hard to “keep up” and hard to stop yourself from comparing your life online to others’. 

With this addiction to social media and lack of identity that comes from God, I’m not shocked to see the spikes of depression in our youth that’s coming alongside a massive identity crisis in our nation. 

Trade your online time for some Bible time. Stop being a slave to the world and social media and choose to be in bondage to Him. Allow yourself to feel the freedom and confidence only He can provide.

When I let go of what others thought of me, both good and bad, it felt like so much weight was lifted from my shoulders. I wasn’t working to please other people. It was so freeing to no longer count on my posts for validation.

My identity and my confidence comes from Him alone.

bump appreciation post… bc it’s Mother’s Day! 🤍
Last year when I became pregnant, God, and this little boy, made me a mother. I’d say today is actually my second Mother’s Day. One year ago I was in my first trimester clinging to my faith and praying non stop over this little growing boy… and nothings changed a year later, I just get peed on  a lot more. 😂 (boy mamas get it)

I didn’t share my pregnancy with the world on purpose but I’m telling you now, pregnancy was AMAZING!! I feel like I’ve been lied to my whole life about how miserable it would be. I loved the process of becoming a mama and to all the women out there, embrace it- it’s one of the most special things you’ll ever do.🤍🤍

Happy Mother’s Day to all the mamas and mamas to be out there!

Just weeks after the Dept of Edu updated its guidance on prayer and other religious expression in public schools, warning school employees not to encourage or endorse such activity, they promote “pride” month. 

The government works for US we should demand better for the future of our children- with the resources our country possess, there’s no reason to have so many students falling behind.

Pray to protect our innocent youth who have to deal with the backwards, and sin filled, priorities that are being pushed our public schools.

Bonus:: when my tweets make it into headlines im just proud of my messaging skills 😆

I love watching you be a Dad. 
Thank God for His will and not my own.

Earlier this year I was humbled to be appointed as a board member of The Jack Brewer Foundation.

JBF is a beacon of hope, serving prisons, orphanages, underserved, and fatherless communities with unwavering dedication. It’s an organization embodying service and compassion. Guided by @jackbrewerbsi ‘s vision, we "Empower from Within," JBF is impacting lives worldwide through various initiatives. With over $70 million in medical aid, orphan care support, and disaster relief efforts, JBF is honoring God and striving to create positive change. I take immense pride in our commitment to a brighter, more compassionate world driven by faith, love, and service.

Please visit The Jack Brewer Foundation online to learn more and to support our upcoming retreat, we are sponsoring 50+ fatherless boys to join our mentors for a retreat in colorado next month! 🙏🏼
2 amazing years. 1 beautiful son. Happy Anniversary to the love of my life ♥️

We spent days pressing Joe Biden who did NOTHING with his resources.. he’s finally sent charter planes (with a very slow pace of moving people… and people still can’t get to the planes) and the kicker is, the passengers will be forced to pay back Biden for these flights. 🤦🏻‍♀️

Really proud to be part of team Mills this week. I’ve been working with Cory for years as he’s cleaned up Biden’s messes. I’ve watched him make the first successful of Americans from the Taliban and now as a sitting member, he’s managed to evacuate 77 Americans out of the Israel, all with his own resources. 

I’ve been busy with all this media but I’ve also had so many producers and reporters thanking the bravery of this team. 🫶🏻
